    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/69a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-19T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2343. For the Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>Is Department to understand that acceptance of <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName>’s reply<note n="6" xml:id="d401fn6">Appendix I to C. F.
                        62, enclosure to Notes of Meeting on June 12, 4 p.m., <ref target="#pg_379"
                            >p. 379</ref>.</note> merely means continuation of present relations
                    with <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> Government or does it
                    convey <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> recognition and further and open
                    extension of support along all lines available?</p>
                <pb facs="0494" n="382" xml:id="pg_382"/>
                <p>Press reports from Paris leave public in doubt on this question. Secretary of War
                    anxious to know whether he should change instructions to <persName
                        corresp="#p_GMGWS1">General Graves</persName>.<note n="7" xml:id="d401fn7"
                        >For reply see telegram from the Commission to Negotiate Peace, no. 2794,
                        June 25, 12 p.m., <ref target="#pg_386">p. 386</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
